# The Frenzied Flame · the yellow chaos that would melt all distinctions

The Frenzied Flame is an Outer God of chaos and undifferentiated oneness — a writhing yellow fire that seeks to melt away all separation, all individuality, all Order, returning everything to the One. Where other powers shape the world, the Frenzied Flame would unmake its very distinctions: no borders, no selves, no Order at all, only the single burning whole.

It burns through eyes. The Three Fingers are its organ, as the Two Fingers are the Greater Will's — a mirrored anatomy of intercession, one hand for Order, one for its dissolution. Through that organ it offers its embrace to a Tarnished.

A Tarnished who takes that embrace can end the world in flame — the bleakest of the game's endings, refused only if Miquella's needle is taken or the path abandoned. Its nature of emergence is ethereal: it is an Outer God, an unseen power beyond the world, half-real until the moment it pours through a bearer's eyes.
